ta on a website without having to reload the entire page to render stuff on the server. and that is possible in CSS, with a bit of help with HTML. without reloading. here's how."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"---"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"\u003Cb style=\"font-size: 125%\"\u003E storage and logic in html\u002Fcss\u003C\u002Fb\u003E"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"you probably already used the dom to store information without even knowing. i've seen a great hack on how to implement tabs with css\u002Fhtml without a single line of js: using `\u003Clabel\u003E`s, `\u003Cinput\u003E`s and the `:checked` pseudoselector."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"it essentially goes like this: you make a radio button for every tab, hide them, and use a selector like `.radio:not(checked)+.tab` to hide unchecked tabs. you can use this to store and check booleans or enums, like this:"}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"\u003Cpre style=\"background-color: rgb(46, 52, 64); color: rgb(216, 222, 233); font-family: &quot;Liga SFMono Nerd Font&quot;, &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, &quot;Fira Code&quot;, Consolas, monospace;\"\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#e8ba36;\"\u003E&lt;\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#81a1c1;\"\u003Ebutton\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#e8ba36;\"\u003E&gt;\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#54a857;\"\u003E&lt;\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#81a1c1;\"\u003Elabel \u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8fbcbb;\"\u003Efor\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#a3be8c;\"\u003E=myBoolean\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#54a857;\"\u003E&gt;\u003C\u002Fspan\u003EClick to toggle\u003Cspan style=\"color:#54a857;\"\u003E&lt;\u002F\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#81a1c1;\"\u003Elabel\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#54a857;\"\u003E&gt;\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003Cspan style=\"color:#e8ba36;\"\u003E&lt;