<!-- --><p><b style="font-size:125%">sending data to a server<!-- --></b></p>
<!-- --><p>this is a bit more tricky, because neither HTML nor CSS have a method that&#x27;s intended for sending stuff to a server without reloading the page when a certain thing happens. but of course there&#x27;s a hack that allows us to do just that: images.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>if you include an image in your HTML file, it gets preloaded, so every request for images is done when the page loads, so we can&#x27;t use that asynchronously. CSS on the other hand can do exactly that: load images when a certain condition, or rather selector, is true. it&#x27;s super simple:<!-- --></p>
